# Telnyx Agent Skills (Cursor)

This project uses **Telnyx Agent Skills** so the AI can write correct Telnyx SDK code. Skills are from the [official Telnyx agent skills repo](https://github.com/team-telnyx/telnyx-ext-agent-skills) and are installed under `.cursor/skills/`.

**Quick start (Telnyx):** https://telnyx.com/resources/ai-agent-skills-claude-code#quick-start-install-in-30-seconds

## In-Project Skills (JavaScript)

Use the following skills when writing Telnyx integrations — they provide SDK setup, examples, and webhook references:

| Skill | Use when |
|-------|----------|
| **telnyx-messaging-javascript** | Send/receive SMS/MMS, opt-outs, messaging numbers |
| **telnyx-messaging-profiles-javascript** | Messaging profiles, number pools, short codes, auto-response |
| **telnyx-voice-javascript** | Call control: dial, answer, hangup, transfer, bridge |
| **telnyx-voice-media-javascript** | Playback, TTS, call recording |
| **telnyx-numbers-javascript** | Search, order, manage phone numbers |
| **telnyx-verify-javascript** | Phone verification, lookup, 2FA |
| **telnyx-ai-assistants-javascript** | AI voice assistants, knowledge bases |
| **telnyx-sip-javascript** | SIP trunking, outbound voice profiles, connections |

## Usage

- When the user asks to send SMS, build IVR, manage numbers, or use Telnyx APIs, **read the relevant skill** from `.cursor/skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md` and follow its setup and code examples.
- Prefer the `telnyx` npm package and the patterns shown in the skills (client init, error handling, webhook verification).
- For more products (10DLC, TeXML, porting, etc.), raw SKILL.md files are available at:
  `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/team-telnyx/telnyx-ext-agent-skills/main/telnyx-javascript/skills/telnyx-{product}-javascript/SKILL.md`

